        public DataLog​(int mutantStatus,
               java.lang.String mutationOperator,
               java.lang.String fileName,
               java.lang.String methodName,
               int lineNumber)
        Constructs the DataLog object
        Parameters:
        mutantStatus - - whether the mutant was killed or not (1 = dead, 0 = alive)
        mutationOperator - - a string representing the type of mutant (e.g. RSK for Remove Synchronized Keyword)
        fileName - - the name of the source code file under mutation testing
        methodName - - the name of the method which was mutated
        lineNumber - - the line number of the mutation

      • logResult

        public void logResult()
               throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a "log.txt" file if the file does not exist, and appends the log entry to the file. "log.txt" is erased during initial startup of ConMuti so that data is not appended to an old run of the program.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - - failed I/O operation when attempting to create the log file
